description: CROQUE MONSIEUR AND MADAME:  A croque monsieur is essentially a grilled ham sandwich on white bread, topped with a creamy, cheesy sauce Mornay and run under the broiler; monsieur's madame gets an extra topping: a sunny-side-up egg.  My favorite croques are not so traditional - they're open-faced, built on solid country bread and found at Le Mabillon (164 boulevard Saint-Germain, Paris 6), a cafe with a rock'n'roll attitude and good salads.
name: Le Mabillion
